Built over ~12 months as a research project into NSE stock prediction. Key learnings: financial time-series are non-stationary, regime changes break most models, and runtime cost of hierarchical transfer learning is significant at scale. 
Preserved as a learning artifact. During this, I learned that its better to model the stock markets using mathematical concepts and forming differential equations for most setups and then create an ecosystem of those. The ML and DL models dont work for stock markets because of the noise and high correlation between the features. The price is also dependent on so many factors and this confuses ML and DL models because at the same time, there can be factors that may point to a bullish signal and there can be another proportion of indicators that may point towards bearishness. Also, to ignore this, we will have to reduce feature sets and this results in underfitting of ML or DL models. Therefore, I personally reached to a conclusion that ML and DL models are not suitable for stock price prediction be it LSTM, be it ensemble models or tree models. The AI models are not capable of predicting the stock markets just yet. 
